This is an example file for creating Kubernetes secrets.
To use this, create a new file named 'secret.yaml' and replace the
placeholder values with your actual credentials.
This file should then be applied using kubectl apply -f secret.yaml.
The actual 'secret.yaml' file should NEVER be committed to version control.
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
name: chatbot-secrets
namespace: awsbedrockworkshop
type: Opaque
stringData:

Root password for the MySQL database
DB_ROOT_PASSWORD: "your_mysql_root_password_here"

Dedicated user and password for the chatbot application
DB_USER: "your_app_username_here"
DB_PASSWORD: "your_app_password_here"

AWS Credentials for connecting to Bedrock
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID: "your_aws_access_key_id_here"
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: "your_aws_secret_access_key_here"